{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Layouts","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/oudscomponents\/layouts"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents"]]},"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","role":"article","title":"Layouts","modules":[{"name":"OUDSComponents"}]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","level":2,"anchor":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"text":"Colored Surface","level":3,"anchor":"Colored-Surface","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_coloredsurface_Orange","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Colored backgrounds use surface colors to maximize the contrast with content."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The colors of several OUDS components (for instance "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSLink","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":") are automatically adjusted if they are placed on "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSColoredSurface","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"To do so, some tokens associated with these specific colors can be customized and are identified with the "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Mono","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" suffix (for instance "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"buttonColorBgDefaultEnabledMono","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" of "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"OrangeThemeButtonComponentTokensProvider","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":")."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":4,"type":"heading","text":"How it works","anchor":"How-it-works"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"According to the color, the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSColoredSurface"},{"type":"text","text":" component adds in SwiftUI environment two flags:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"oudsUseMonochrome","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": to inform a component that needs to use mono version of tokens"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"oudsOnColoredSurface"},{"text":": to inform a component it is placed on colored surface even if the mono is off","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"level":4,"type":"heading","text":"How to use","anchor":"How-to-use"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["    \/\/ The folowing view has a colored background \"modeOnStatusPositiveEmphasized\" with","    \/\/ - a text with the color adapted according to the adjusted colorScheme      ","    \/\/ - a button that uses the mono version of tokens","","    \/\/ As view","    OUDSColoredSurface(color: theme.colorModes.modeOnStatusPositiveEmphasized) {","        VStack {","            Text(\"Status Positive Emphasized\")","            .oudsForegroundColor(theme.colors.colorContentDefault)","","            OUDSButton(text: \"Button\") {}","        }","    }","","    \/\/ As view modifier","","    VStack {","        Text(\"Status Positive Emphasized\")","        .oudsForegroundColor(theme.colors.colorContentDefault)","","        OUDSButton(text: \"Button\") {}","    }","    .oudsColoredSurface(theme.colorModes.modeOnStatusPositiveEmphasized)"]},{"level":4,"type":"heading","text":"Debuging contrast ratios","anchor":"Debuging-contrast-ratios"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Some countries set up new laws so as to force companies to have a better accessibility of their digital services."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This is for example the case for France with the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/accessibilite.numerique.gouv.fr\/"},{"type":"text","text":", also named “RGAA”."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The WCAG specifications, for AA level, defines a contrast ratio of 4.5:1 for textual elements (i.e. texts), and 3:1 for non-textual elements (i.e. link’s chevron)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"However it is highly recommended for mobile devices to reach AAA level because of the screen sizes and luminosity issues, i.e. 7:1 for texts and 4.5:1 for non-textual elements."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Some components like ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSLink","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" can be used on ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSColoredSurface","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" ; thus in that case we can know the surface color for a given component on it, and compute the contrast ratio, and in the end display or not warnings.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To do that, some steps must be followed in your component implementation:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Rise the flag to allow debugging (e.g. i #DEBUG mode)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Get the environement variable defined by the colored surface containing the applied color","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In the component implementation, add a line of code comparing the color to test and that surface"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Then keep an eye on your logs ; warnings will be added there if WCAG 2.1 3:1, 4.5:1 or 7:1 ratios are not reached, depending to the methods you call"}]}]}]},{"code":["\/\/ Rise the flag","#if DEBUG","OUDSWCAG21Ratios.oudsDebugWCAG21Colors = true","#endif","","\/\/ Supposing we are in your component View \/ ViewModifer struct","","\/\/ Get the applied surface color","@Environment(\\.oudsSurfaceColor) var surfaceColor","","\/\/ In the function defining the color to apply, add the line below","\/\/ where colorTokenToApply is the color to apply from a theme:","","\/\/ Non-textual components, in AA","OUDSWCAG21Ratios.debugContrastRatio(colorToApply, surfaceColor, .nonTextual)","","\/\/ Textual components and AAA to check","OUDSWCAG21Ratios.debugContrastRatio(colorToApply, surfaceColor, .AAA)"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"anchor":"Divider","text":"Divider","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"anchor":"How-it-works","text":"How it works","level":4,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_coloredsurface_Orange"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A divider is used to separate content elements in a view. Two kinds of divider are proposed:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSHorizontalDivider","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":": to separate elements stacked vertivally (VStask).","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSVerticalDivider"},{"type":"text","text":": to separate elements stacked Horizontally (HStask)."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A divider can be colored using color enumerated in the ","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSDividerColor","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"How-to-use","text":"How to use","level":4,"type":"heading"},{"code":["\/\/ Add a vertical divider between items","HStack {","    Text(\"Hello wolrd!\")","    OUDSVerticalDivider(color: .brandPrimary)","    Text(\"Happy to see you\")","}","","\/\/ Add an horizontal divider between items","VStack {","    Text(\"Hello wolrd!\")","    OUDSHorizontalDivider(color: .brandPrimary)","    Text(\"Happy to see you\")","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"}]}],"kind":"article","abstract":[{"text":"Some components can be used for ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"layouts","type":"text"}]},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"references":{"doc://OUDSComponents/documentation/OUDSComponents/OUDSButton":{"url":"\/documentation\/oudscomponents\/oudsbutton","title":"OUDSButton","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"OUDSButton","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"OUDSButton","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton"},{"type":"text","text":" proposes layout with text only, icon only or text with icon."}],"role":"symbol"},"doc://OUDSComponents/documentation/OUDSComponents/OUDSLink":{"type":"topic","title":"OUDSLink","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSLink"},{"type":"text","text":" proposes layout with text only or text with icon."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It also proposes layout to navigate forward or backward. The link can be displayed in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"small"},{"type":"tex